fields.description:
Currently, remotes of a repo are displayed in alphabetical order.
However, "origin" and "default" respectively for git and hg are special remote names. 
When managing several remotes with different purpose, I think it would be easier to see what is or not a special remote if special remotes were displayed a bit differently.

Suggestions:
 - make origin/default always on top in the list of remotes;
 - display special remotes in bold characters (or italic, or colored or a mix);
